Defendant Benjamin D Freeman in court with attorney Craig Michael Kuhary.  Pablo Galaviz appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case called for sentencing hearing. State presents statements. Defense presents statements.   The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

 Ct. 1 6 months jail
 Ct. 2 3 months jail
 Ct. 3 30 days jail
Sentences to run consecutive to each other

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEAR(S); on each count to run concurrent with each other

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 on each count (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 on each count (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME:  45 days jail on count 1, STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.
